[src:semidefinite-programming/definite-matrix] In other words, a Hermitian matrix is positive-definite if and only if it defines an inner product.
[src:semidefinite-programming/definite-matrix] Positive-definite and positive-semidefinite matrices can be characterized in many ways, which may explain the importance of the concept in various parts of mathematics.
