[src:semidefinite-programming/semidefinite-programming] The weak duality theorem states that the value of the primal SDP is at least the value of the dual SDP.
[src:semidefinite-programming/semidefinite-programming] Therefore, any feasible solution to the dual SDP lower-bounds the primal SDP value, and conversely, any feasible solution to the primal SDP upper-bounds the dual SDP value.
