[src:semidefinite-programming/semidefinite-programming] A sufficient condition for strong duality to hold for a SDP problem (and in general, for any convex optimization problem) is the Slater's condition.
[src:semidefinite-programming/semidefinite-programming] It is also possible to attain strong duality for SDPs without additional regularity conditions by using an extended dual problem proposed by Ramana.
